\naccurate estimation of the OG. The model itself only requires AO telemetry data\nto derive statistical information on atmospheric turbulence. Furthermore, we\nshow that by only using an estimation of the current Fried parameter r_0 and\nthe basic system-level characteristics, OGs can be estimated with an accuracy\nof less than 10%. Finally, we highlight the importance of OG estimation in the\ncase of NCPA compensation. The proposed method is applied to the PyWFS.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Jun 2020 11:38:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 15 Jul 2020 11:53:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-25"}
