al Geopotential Models are central in the modelling of geopotential for the\npurposes of the IHRF. I present a set of correction formulas that can be used\nto move to the zero-tide model before, in the middle, or after the processing,\nand finally to the mean-tide IHRF. To reduce the confusion around the multitude\nof tidal systems I propose that modelling should primarily done in the\nzero-tide system, with the mean-tide potential as an add-on.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Jun 2020 14:38:29 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 2 Nov 2020 09:49:54 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 22 Jun 2021 16:30:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-22"}
