$^{-1}$ and the central magnetic field in the range 10-40\n$\\mu$G. The resulting $\\gamma$-ray fluxes calculated assuming these model\nparameters do not violate the upper limits on $\\gamma$-ray diffuse emission set\nby the Fermi-LAT telescope. Further studies are now required to explore the\nconsistency of these large magnetic fields with Faraday rotation studies and to\nstudy the interplay between the secondary electrons and the ICM turbulence.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Jun 2020 13:49:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-12"}
